# Baked Pears with Cinnamon

Based on [Healthy Baked Pears with Cinnamon - Running on Real Food](https://runningonrealfood.com/healthy-baked-pears) ([wayback](http://web.archive.org/web/20250918122542/https://runningonrealfood.com/healthy-baked-pears/))

{ rating="0" image="None" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

- [ ] Ripe pears (as many as desired)
- [ ] 1/2 tsp maple syrup per half pear
- [ ] 1/4 tsp cinnamon per half pear

### Optional Toppings

- [ ] Coconut yogurt
- [ ] Nuts
- [ ] Granola
- [ ] Whipped cream

## Recipe

1. Preheat oven to 350F.
1. Slice pears in half and gently scoop out seeds using a small cookie scoop or spoon.
1. Place pear halves cut-side up on a baking pan or oven-proof dish.
1. Drizzle each pear half with 1/2 tsp maple syrup and sprinkle with 1/4 tsp cinnamon.
1. Bake until soft and tender, approximately 25-30 minutes.
1. Serve warm with desired toppings.

## Notes

1. Anjou and Bosc varieties are top picks for baking as they hold their shape and texture best
1. Suggested serving size: 1 pear half
1. Per serving (1 pear half): 63 calories, 15g carbs, 0.5g protein, 3.5g fiber
1. Leftovers can be refrigerated for 2-3 days and served cold over waffles, pancakes, or oatmeal
1. Minimal added sugar - relies on natural sweetness of pears
1. Serves 4 pear halves
